When my dad even tried to speak sternly to me she would tell him to “leave her baby alone”. She always said I had more sense than the adults and I was always her favorite person no matter who else was in the room. Her world stopped for me, and mine revolved around her.

She used to clear her desk at work or push two chairs together so I could take a nap. One winter it snowed and she said it was too much snow and too cold for me to go outside so they brought the snow inside to me in a kiddie pool and I played inside.

When I was a baby she apparently wore a literal pin with my face on it everyday. When I got older and lived further her and my grandpa used to have a birthday cake for me every time I came to visit them no matter how far it was from my birthday.

When I was little she would put coffee and milk (mainly milk) in my sippy cup so I could be like her. I would ask to see her every single day, and it didn’t matter if she was working or what she was doing she would always tell my parents “bring my baby to me”.

I’m going to turn this into a thread of my memories of her. Because I always feel like I don’t remember enough because she was sick for so long but I know it’s a coping mechanism. Today I want to focus on what I do remember and share her with y’all. Cause she was the best.
